  <div class="doc-title">Transactions tab — iOS</div>
  <div class="doc-subtitle">The list of every transaction the user has captured, with search, filtering, row interactions, and entry points for adding and reviewing. Built for iOS where bank SMS is not auto-read — captures come via the Shortcut or manual entry.</div>

  <div class="doc-info">
    <div class="doc-info-cell">
      <div class="info-label">The problem</div>
      <div class="info-body">
        On iOS we cannot read bank SMS automatically. The Transactions tab has to do double duty: be the home for everything the user has captured, and also explain why the list might be empty without making the user feel the app is broken. The empty states must reframe the iOS reality — Shortcut + manual — as the path, not as a failure. Detail editing, internal-transfer flagging, and category creation also live here and must feel light, not bureaucratic.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="doc-info-cell">
      <div class="info-label">Flows in this document</div>
      <div class="flow-list">
        <div class="flow-list-item">Default tab — list with rows, search, filters</div>
        <div class="flow-list-item">Empty states — Shortcut not set, set + waiting, manual-only, first session</div>
        <div class="flow-list-item">No-results — search, filter, range</div>
        <div class="flow-list-item">Connectivity — loading, error, offline</div>
        <div class="flow-list-item">Transaction detail — view, edit, internal-transfer, delete + undo</div>
        <div class="flow-list-item">Add transaction — sheet, validation, soft warning</div>
        <div class="flow-list-item">Review transaction — uncategorised flow</div>
        <div class="flow-list-item">Category picker — search, type-ahead, create new</div>
        <div class="flow-list-item">Centre [+] action sheet</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

