  <div class="handoff-sec">
    <div class="handoff-h">Accessibility</div>
    <ul class="handoff-list">
      <li><strong>Touch targets — 44×44px minimum</strong> on every interactive element. Filter chips, date presets, type tabs, the centre [+], the close ✕ on every sheet, the toast Undo, and the Edit/Delete pill buttons all need to clear this.</li>
      <li><strong>Contrast — 4.5:1 minimum for text</strong>, 7:1 for financial figures (the big amount on the detail sheet, transaction-row amounts). Check the de-emphasised internal-transfer amount carefully — grey-on-light loses contrast fastest.</li>
      <li><strong>Never colour-only for state.</strong> Income amounts have the green colour <em>and</em> a leading "+". Internal-transfer rows are greyed <em>and</em> labelled "Internal transfer · not counted". The "Needs category" pill carries text, not just gold colour. Disabled CTAs need a text or icon signal alongside the grey fill.</li>
      <li><strong>Focus order — top-to-bottom, including on RTL.</strong> Range pill → search → tabs → list. Inside sheets: header → amount → field rows in order → primary CTA → destructive action. RTL flips the visual direction but not the focus order.</li>
      <li><strong>"Needs category" rows must announce as a single unit</strong> to screen readers — merchant, amount, and "Needs category" together — not three separate fields.</li>
    </ul>
